item.title: About
item.description: I am a graduate student in CSAIL/EECS department at MIT started in Fall 2019. I am fortunate to be advised by Stefanie Jegelka. I did my undergraduate in Mathematics and Computer Science1 from 2016 to 2019 at UIUC where I was fortunate to work with Tandy Warnow and her students on computational phylogenetics. Before that, I worked briefly in system biology with P.I. Imoukhuede. Contact 32-G416 MIT Stata Center 32 Vassar St Cambridge, MA 02139
